    <title>Galois closures and elementary components of Hilbert schemes of points</title>
    <summary>  Bhargava and the first-named author of this paper introduced a functorial
Galois closure operation for finite-rank ring extensions, generalizing
constructions of Grothendieck and Katz--Mazur. In this paper, we apply Galois
closures to construct a new infinite family of irreducible components of
Hilbert schemes of points. We show that these components are elementary, in the
sense that they parametrize algebras supported at a point.
</summary>
